commitResults.messageTitle: Add command echoing and exit on 'bye' command
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit introduces a new feature that echoes commands entered by
user in the command-line. Application exits when user types 'bye'
Rename function to better describe its functionality

Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display
them back to the user when requested.
Create a Task class to represent tasks

commitResults.messageTitle: Add mark, unmark and print functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit implements ability to mark and unmark tasks, along with a
new feature to print tasks with its status icon.

commitResults.messageTitle: Apply Google Java Style Guide and CS2113 Java Coding Standard to JunBot.java and Task.java
commitResults.messageBody:
Follow consistent coding practices by standardizing indentation,
spacing, and naming conventions

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Todo, Event and Deadlines functions
commitResults.messageBody:
Add todo class for user to add task without dates. Add event class for
user to add task with start and end dates. Add deadlines class for
user to add task with end date.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor mark and unmark function to use isValidListPosition function
commitResults.messageBody:
Add a common Boolean function to determine if user input
has a valid list number for mark and unmark functions
